SIMPLE: nourish
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nourish
<hw>Nour"ish</hw> <pr>(n⟦ucr⟧r"⟦icr⟧sh)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Nourished</conjf>
<pr>(n⟦ucr⟧r"⟦icr⟧sht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Nourishing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>norisen</ets>,
<ets>norischen</ets>, OF. <ets>nurir</ets>, <ets>nurrir</ets>,
<ets>norir</ets>, F. <ets>nourrir</ets>, fr. L. <ets>nutrire</ets>. Cf.
<er>Nurse</er>, <er>Nutriment</er>, and see <er>-ish</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To feed and cause to grow; to supply with matter
which increases bulk or supplies waste, and promotes health; to furnish
with nutriment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He planteth an ash, and the rain doth <qex>nourish</qex> it.</q>
<rj><qau>Is. xliv. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To support; to maintain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Whiles I in Ireland <qex>nourish</qex> a mighty band.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To supply the means of support and increase to; to
encourage; to foster; <as>as, to <ex>nourish</ex> rebellion; to
<ex>nourish</ex> the virtues.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Nourish</xex> their
contentions.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To cherish; to comfort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ye have <qex>nourished</qex> your hearts.</q> <rj><qau>James v.
5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To educate; to instruct; to bring up; to nurture; to
promote the growth of in attainments.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Nourished</qex> up in the words of faith.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim.
iv. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To cherish; feed; supply. See
<er>Nurture</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nourish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nourish
<hw>Nour"ish</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To promote growth;
to furnish nutriment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Grains and roots <qex>nourish</qex> more than their leaves.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To gain nourishment.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nourish</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Nourish
<hw>Nour"ish</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A nurse.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hoolland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nourishable</ent>⟦br⟧
